<body>
  <header></header>
  <main class="start-team-page">
    <div class="container start-team-shell">
      <a href="/start-team" class="btn btn-secondary back-button">&larr; Back to Steps</a>
      <p class="step-label">Step 6 of 6</p>
      <h1>Learn &amp; Prepare</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Begin programming and mechanical development for competition.</p>
      <section class="content-section">
        <h3 style="text-align:center; color:var(--accent-primary);">CAD Design</h3>
        <p>Use <a href="https://www.onshape.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Onshape</a> for CAD design. Onshape is free for students and teams, making it the perfect tool for designing robot parts and assemblies.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Follow Onshape's tutorials on their website to learn the basics</li>
          <li>Start by designing simple parts, then move to full robot assemblies</li>
          <li>Use Onshape's built-in tutorials for guidance</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="text-align:center; color:var(--accent-primary);">Programming</h3>
        <p>Learn FTC programming with these excellent resources:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://firstinspires.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GM0 (Game Manual 0)</a> – Comprehensive FTC knowledge base with tutorials and best practices</li>
          <li><a href="https://www.nextftc.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Next FTC</a> – Advanced programming guides and strategies</li>
          <li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/c/BrogAnnaPratt" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BrogAnna Pratt's YouTube Channel</a> – Video tutorials for FTC programming and debugging</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="text-align:center; color:var(--accent-primary);">Building</h3>
        <p>You don't need a detailed tutorial for building — it's mostly about screwing parts together and assembling your robot. Start with your kit's assembly instructions and learn as you build. Most of the learning happens through hands-on assembly and testing.</p>
        <p><strong>Action:</strong> Start learning with tutorials on the supplier websites, dive into GM0 and Next FTC for programming concepts, and begin building your robot with your team!</p>
      </section>
      <div class="step-actions">
        <a href="/start-team" class="btn btn-primary">Done! Start Your Team &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <script src="/assets/js/main.js?v=37"></script>
